Remarks:
This species is similar to 

Eburia
(
Eburia
) 
macrotaenia
Bates, 1880

(
Fig. 1A and 1B
), but 

E.
(
E.
) 
angeldiazi


sp. nov.

differs as follows: frons with corono-frontal suture moderately defined (
Fig. 2A
); antennal tubercles with apex obliquely, acute, widely sulcate (
Fig 2A
); pronotum with central lateral tubercles very acute toward apex (
Fig. 2B
); with pronotal disk with three tubercles without gibba (
Fig. 2B
); the outermost anterior eburneous maculae starts from base of elytra, and outermost posterior eburneous maculae 1.5 times longer than innermost (
Fig. 2C
); metafemora with short spiniform projection, shorter than width of femora (
Fig. 3A
). In 

E.
(
E.
) 
macrotaenia

frons with corono-frontal suture very distinct, wide (
Fig. 2D
); antennal tubercles with apex truncate (
Fig 2D
); pronotum with central lateral tubercles moderately, apically obtuse (
Fig. 2E
); with pronotal disk with three tubercles and two gibba (
Fig. 2E
); the outermost anterior eburneous maculae not starts from base of elytra, and outermost posterior eburneous maculae two times longer than innermost (
Fig. 2F
); metafemora with long spiniform projection, longer than width of femora (
Fig. 3C
); and the male genitalia differs from the 

E.
(
E.
) 
angeldiazi


sp. nov.

(
Fig. 3D
).
